# MCP Remote SSH Server Configuration
#
# This file configures the connection to your remote GPU machine.
# Copy this to .env and fill in your values.

# Quick Setup
# -----------
# Use the setup script (recommended):
#   ./scripts/setup-mcp-env.sh
#
# The script will detect your SSH configuration and guide you through setup.

# SSH Configuration
# -----------------
# The MCP server needs direct SSH access. For SkyPilot clusters that use
# ProxyCommand (jump hosts), you need to set up an SSH tunnel first.

# Method 1: Direct SSH (no ProxyCommand)
# ---------------------------------------
# If you have direct SSH access, use the actual hostname/port:
#
# SSH_HOST=user@hostname
# SSH_PORT=22
# SSH_KEY_PATH=/path/to/key  # Optional

# Method 2: SSH Tunnel (for ProxyCommand/jump hosts)
# ---------------------------------------------------
# For SkyPilot clusters that use ProxyCommand, you need an SSH tunnel.
#
# 1. Check if you need a tunnel:
#    ssh -G <cluster-name> | grep proxycommand
#    (If you see "proxycommand", you need a tunnel)
#
# 2. Start the SSH tunnel (keep running in a separate terminal):
#    ssh -N -L 10022:localhost:10022 <cluster-name>
#
# 3. Configure MCP to use the tunnel:
SSH_HOST=root@localhost
SSH_PORT=10022

# Getting Your Configuration
# --------------------------
# Option A: Use the setup script (easiest)
#   ./scripts/setup-mcp-env.sh
#
# Option B: Manual setup
#   1. Find your cluster: sky status
#   2. Check configuration: ssh -G <cluster-name>
#   3. If ProxyCommand exists, set up tunnel (see Method 2 above)
#   4. Update SSH_HOST and SSH_PORT above
#   5. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
